<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Height determination for block-level non-replaced elements in normal flow</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#normal-block" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify that the height is the distance between the top border edge of the top most block-level child box that doesn't have margins collapsed, and the bottom border edge of the bottommost block-level child that doesn't have margins collapsed. When a block-level non-replaced element is in normal flow, overflow does not compute to visible but has been propagated to the viewport and the height is auto." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                overflow: visible;
                border: 3px solid black;
                background: green;
            }
            #d2
            {
                border: 1px solid blue;
                background: blue;
                height: 25px;
                margin-top: 25px;
            }
            #d3
            {
                height: 25px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the green boxes above and below the blue box have the same height.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2"></div>
            <div id="d3"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>